{
  "local_port": 47610,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to check your PF balance?",
  "response": "To check your Provident Fund (PF) balance in India, you can use several methods. Here is a step-by-step guide on how to do it:\n\n### 1. **Using the UMANG App**\nThe UMANG (Unified Mobile Application for New-age Governance) app allows you to access various government services, including EPFO services.\n\n- **Step 1:** Download and install the UMANG app from the Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n- **Step 2:** Register using your mobile number.\n- **Step 3:** Select 'EPFO' from the services list.\n- **Step 4:** Choose 'Employee Centric Services'.\n- **Step 5:** Click on 'View Passbook'.\n- **Step 6:** Enter your UAN (Universal Account Number) and request an OTP (One-Time Password) to be sent to your registered mobile number.\n- **Step 7:** Enter the OTP and submit to view your PF passbook.\n\n### 2. **Using the EPFO Website**\nYou can also check your PF balance directly on the EPFO (Employees' Provident Fund Organization) website.\n\n- **Step 1:** Visit the EPFO member e-Sewa portal at [www.epfindia.gov.in](www.epfindia.gov.in).\n- **Step 2:** Click on 'For Employees' under 'Our Services'.\n- **Step 3:** Select 'Member Passbook' from the dropdown menu.\n- **Step 4:** Enter your UAN and password to log in.\n- **Step 5:** After logging in, you will be able to see your passbook and check your PF balance.\n\n### 3. **Using Missed Call Service**\nEPFO also provides a missed call service to check your PF balance.\n\n- **Step 1:** From your registered mobile number, give a missed call to 9966044425.\n- **Step 2:** The call will automatically disconnect after two rings, and you will receive an SMS with your PF account balance details.\n\n### 4. **Using SMS Service**\nYou can also check your PF balance by sending an SMS.\n\n- **Step 1:** From your registered mobile number, send an SMS to 7738299899.\n- **Step 2:** The format of the SMS should be: `EPFOHO UAN ENG`.\n  - `EPFOHO` is the code for EPFO head office.\n  - `UAN` is your Universal Account Number.\n  - `ENG` specifies the language as English (you can replace ENG with HIN for Hindi or other supported language codes).\n- **Step 3:** You will receive an SMS with your PF account balance.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- Ensure that your UAN is activated and your mobile number is linked to your UAN.\n- If you face any issues, you can reach out to the EPFO helpline at 1800118005.\n\nUsing any of these methods, you can easily check your PF balance.",
